race.comment: ABOVE ME (2) made good progress last start narrowly beaten at Bendigo. It was a strong effort after an awkward start. Will be peaking and finds an easier assignment. FROSTED IN TIME (1) resumed and led unexpectedly when beaten a lip at Kilmore when last seen. Will be naturally improved and is a winnable race. VANGOGH BANKCHEQUE (10) debuts for the Kennewell yard with the blinkers applied. Placed in her most recent Cranbourne jumpout and looks to have her share of ability.  Draws the carpark and will need some luck. SMUGGLERS SPOT (9) has won a jumpout since his solid debut and should be around the mark.
